{
    "name": "Menemen",
    "instructions": "1. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add onion, bell pepper, chiles, and red pepper flakes. Cook and stir until onions are soft and translucent, about 5 to 6 minutes.\n\n2. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.\n\n3. Add tomatoes, with their juices, and season with salt and pepper. Cook until tomatoes are softened, about 4 to 6 minutes.\n\n4. Add eggs to the skillet, tilting the skillet until eggs cover skillet completely. Do not mix. Cook until eggs are set, about 3 to 5 minutes.\n\n5. Top with basil and feta cheese.",
